{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Pin down triage output attachment format in persisted verdict with a concrete worked example.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["f4734a05d9e8bc7f4","f3669200f8b7b8cc3","f1411f610e5a24aa7"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"triage output attachment format in persisted verdict"},{"coaching":"Plan how sidecar payload field enumeration contract will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["f71a4181699981a5d"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"sidecar payload field enumeration contract"},{"coaching":"Pin down move-less advisory triage list entry structure with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fe7c2e08dcbaf69db"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"move-less advisory triage list entry structure"},{"coaching":"Pin down triage stamp schema contract and validation boundary with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fbbf813dbfb96ed83"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"triage stamp schema contract and validation boundary"},{"coaching":"Plan how AC5 documentation compliance verification method will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f90c0fed7621c148f","f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"AC5 documentation compliance verification method"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] DET-tier block_threshold fallback behavior will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fe94e7dc4968c8627"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"DET-tier block_threshold fallback behavior"},{"coaching":"Pin down first criteria id definition for multi-element lists with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fea1b8769f88cfecf"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"first criteria id definition for multi-element lists"},{"coaching":"Realign placement outside move registry vs parent mechanism to the parent's plan — the parent wins on conflict; if the parent is genuinely wrong, update the PARENT first (which forces its re-review), never silently diverge the leaf.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f452324b5abfcb02c"],"move_id":"13","move_name":"realign to parent plan","subject":"placement outside move registry vs parent mechanism"},{"coaching":"Realign omitted advisory-count threshold guard from parent to the parent's plan — the parent wins on conflict; if the parent is genuinely wrong, update the PARENT first (which forces its re-review), never silently diverge the leaf.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fc9d357805844c42d"],"move_id":"13","move_name":"realign to parent plan","subject":"omitted advisory-count threshold guard from parent"},{"coaching":"Weigh at least one structural alternative for automated vs author-driven triage semantic choice.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f89f0df104b8fc8a9"],"move_id":"5","move_name":"weigh alternatives","subject":"automated vs author-driven triage semantic choice"},{"coaching":"Record an ADR for schema rollback and forward-compatibility of triage fields — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f8a959d6f9c97517e"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"schema rollback and forward-compatibility of triage fields"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":13,"blocking":2,"dropped":14,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":5,"ran":true,"references":5,"resolved":3,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":2},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":6118,"file_impact":3,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":48,"verify_lint_abstained":48},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1545,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":3,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":309.6,"llm_calls":29,"llm_ms":603671.1,"total_ms":604107.2,"verify_requests":31},"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"sidecar_baseline":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T2","T4","T5a","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] State the default output format for triage results in the plan — e.g., 'a `triage` key added to each advisory finding's dict in the persisted verdict JSON, plus a rendered Markdown block appended to the coaching section' — so the executor has a concrete, actionable default.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'the triage list is attached to the plan-review coaching output (each surviving-advisory coach note gains `triage` + optional `triage_reason`; advisories that mapped to no coach move still appear in the triage list keyed by finding id), and rendered in the review's coaching section' — 'attached' and 'rendered' are described but the structural form (dict field on the verdict object, a rendered Markdown string, a dedicated section key) is not specified.","The What section specifies the defer-reason string format via example but not the envelope that carries it into the persisted verdict or the human-readable coaching section."],"finding":"The plan does not specify the output format/structure by which the triage stage's results are attached to the coaching output in the persisted verdict — an executor implementing `workflow_ops.py` must choose whether to append a Markdown block, add a structured JSON field, or both, with no stated default.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4734a05d9e8bc7f4","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope — `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/workflow_ops.py`; What section — 'attached to the plan-review coaching output'","norm_id":"n60afea3e89b76d7e","priority":0.67,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["One executor adds a top-level `triage` list to the JSON verdict object; another appends a Markdown table to the coaching prose — both satisfy 'attached' and 'rendered' but produce incompatible artifacts, breaking downstream consumers or R7's metric collection."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add `sidecar.py` to scope: extend `build_payload`'s coaching-note enumeration (lines 503–514) to include `triage` and `triage_reason` fields so the annotation survives into the persisted REVIEW_RESULT payload.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["sidecar.py lines 503–514: `build_payload` emits coaching as `{move_id, move_name, subject, finding_refs, coaching, decision}` — a closed enumeration, not a passthrough.","Plan states: 'the annotation reaches the persisted verdict' and 'each surviving-advisory coach note gains `triage` + optional `triage_reason`'.","ABSENCE: `sidecar.py` is not listed in the Scope section."],"finding":"`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py` is an unenumerated consumer: its `build_payload()` explicitly enumerates coaching-note fields (move_id, move_name, subject, finding_refs, coaching, decision) with individual `.get()` calls, so a new `triage`/`triage_reason` stamp added to coaching notes will be silently dropped from the persisted REVIEW_RESULT sidecar payload — contradicting the plan's claim that 'the annotation reaches the persisted verdict'.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f71a4181699981a5d","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section / src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py:503-514","norm_id":"n6b6c81d9ab75805a","priority":1.0,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["The triage stamp is added to coaching notes in plan_review_coach but sidecar.build_payload silently discards it — R7's advisory-application-latency metric, which depends on reading the persisted triage field, would see null values for all reviews.","test_audit_coaching_fidelity.py pins the exact coaching note fields (lines 42–49) and would not catch this gap."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"In `sidecar.py` `build_payload`, add `\"triage\": c.get(\"triage\"), \"triage_reason\": c.get(\"triage_reason\")` to the per-coaching-note dict. Also add `sidecar.py` to the Scope section.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"high","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the verdict dict key (e.g. a new `triage` top-level list) and the object schema for triage entries that cover advisory findings receiving no coach move, including required fields (finding_id, triage, triage_reason?) and how it relates to the existing `coaching` list.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'advisories that mapped to no coach move still appear in the triage list keyed by finding id'","finalize_verdict in orchestrator.py (lines 531-544) returns a fixed dict with keys: verdict, ticket_id, ticket_type, blocking, advisory, coaching, overflow, indeterminate, dropped, coverage, runner, model — no triage key","The plan does not name a new verdict key (e.g. 'triage') and does not say whether no-move advisories are embedded in the existing 'coaching' list or emitted as a sibling key","ABSENCE: no schema shape is defined for the keyed-by-finding-id entries (e.g. {finding_id, triage, triage_reason?})"],"finding":"The plan introduces a triage list for advisory findings that received NO coach move ('advisories that mapped to no coach move still appear in the triage list keyed by finding id'), but never specifies the verdict dict key where this list is placed, nor the object shape of entries in it. The existing verdict shape (finalize_verdict in orchestrator.py) has no `triage` key, and the plan names no new top-level key to add.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe7c2e08dcbaf69db","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'advisories that mapped to no coach move still appear in the triage list keyed by finding id'; Scope: passes.py / workflow_ops.py","norm_id":"n62ef36c7a071454c","priority":0.67,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer must decide: does the no-coach-move triage entry go into `coaching` as a special note shape, into `advisory` finding annotations, or into a new `triage` key? The ambiguity means two implementations can produce byte-different output and both claim to satisfy the plan.","A consumer (e.g. R7 metric collection) reading the verdict cannot know where to find triage entries for unmapped advisories without a spec."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify explicitly whether `triage` / `triage_reason` are added to the Pass-4 `CoachNote` structured-output contract (requiring a schema change) or stamped onto rendered note dicts post-`render_coach_notes` (a pure Python annotation), and co-locate this decision with the relevant schema in passes.py.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'each surviving-advisory coach note gains `triage` + optional `triage_reason`'","passes.py lines 189-199: CoachNote pydantic model has only move_id, subject, finding_refs — no triage fields","render_coach_notes in coach.py (lines 162-196) produces notes with keys: move_id, move_name, subject, finding_refs, coaching, and optionally decision — no triage fields","ABSENCE: the plan never says 'add triage and triage_reason to CoachNote' or 'stamp triage onto the rendered note dict post render_coach_notes'"],"finding":"The `triage` stamp (values: `apply-now` | `defer`) added to coach notes and the `triage_reason` optional field are not specified as additions to any schema contract. The plan's existing `_pass4_model` CoachNote in passes.py has `move_id`, `subject`, `finding_refs` — no `triage` or `triage_reason` — and the plan does not say whether to add these fields to the Pass-4 output contract or treat them as post-render annotations.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fbbf813dbfb96ed83","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'each surviving-advisory coach note gains triage + optional triage_reason'; Scope: passes.py _pass4_model / render_coach_notes","norm_id":"n7ce644e3824e4ec1","priority":0.536,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer adding triage to the output contract (CoachNote) changes the structured-output schema the LLM must conform to, potentially inducing hallucinated triage values from the model — violating the plan's 'no LLM judgment' guarantee.","An implementer stamping triage post-render (in workflow_ops) is safe but inconsistent with the plan's statement that render_coach_notes 'already adds' the decision stamp — the placement of the analogous triage stamp is ambiguous."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Stamp triage post-render (analogous to the guide_url annotation in finalize_verdict lines 525-530), explicitly calling this out in the Scope section as 'triage stamped onto rendered notes after render_coach_notes, not part of the CoachNote LLM contract'.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a proving command to AC5 that asserts the required content is present in `docs/plan-review-gate.md`, e.g., `grep -qE 'APPLY_NOW_MARGIN' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -qE 'defer.*priority.*block' docs/plan-review-gate.md && echo PASS`.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC5 reads: 'docs/plan-review-gate.md documents the triage stage, its ranking rule (the APPLY_NOW_MARGIN default, the ordering, the defer-reason format), and the R7 dogfood expectation' — no 'Proving command:' line is present, unlike ACs 1–4.","All other testable ACs carry a 'Proving command: python -m pytest ...' line; AC5 and AC6 do not carry a targeted doc-check command."],"finding":"AC5 (docs) has no proving command — it states what the documentation must contain but provides no concrete check (e.g., a grep or script) that would produce evidence of compliance in-session.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f90c0fed7621c148f","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC5: 'docs/plan-review-gate.md documents the triage stage...'","norm_id":"n3ba3a09f44104f7c","priority":0.44,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor marks AC5 done after adding a one-sentence mention of the triage stage, without capturing the margin default, ordering rule, or defer-reason format — the AC cannot be objectively falsified without a command."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Proving command: `grep -qE 'APPLY_NOW_MARGIN' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -qE 'priority.*block_threshold' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -qE 'advisory-application-latency' docs/plan-review-gate.md && echo PASS`","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["1 criterion line(s) bundle multiple deliverables with 'and' (split so each is independently verifiable).","vague/subjective terms present: clean"],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add at least one AC (with a proving command) verifying that the assembled coaching output contains the `triage` stamp on surviving-advisory coach notes and that advisories without a move appear in the triage list keyed by finding id, covering the workflow_ops.py wiring described in Scope.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"each surviving-advisory coach note gains `triage` + optional `triage_reason`; advisories that mapped to no coach move still appear in the triage list keyed by finding id), and rendered in the review's coaching section\"","ABSENCE: no AC line verifies that the triage annotation appears on coach notes or that the coaching-section output contains the triage list"],"finding":"The 'What' section describes two output-side deliverables — (1) each surviving-advisory coach note gains a `triage` stamp (plus optional `triage_reason`), and (2) the triage list is 'rendered in the review's coaching section' — but no acceptance criterion covers either the annotation of coach notes or the rendering of the triage list in the coaching output.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3669200f8b7b8cc3","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section (final paragraph: 'The triage list is attached to the plan-review coaching output...'); Acceptance Criteria (no covering AC)","norm_id":"n364ad7f01fd4c2ba","priority":0.385,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer completes the triage_advisories pure function and all four unit tests pass, but forgets to wire the triage stamp back onto the coach notes or into the rendered coaching section — all ACs still pass because they test the function in isolation.","The workflow_ops.py wiring step is incomplete: triage results are computed but not persisted to the verdict, leaving the feature invisible to the end user."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify whether DET-tier advisory findings (which have no `block_threshold` field and hardcoded `priority=0.4` from `partition_findings`) should use the criterion's registry `block_threshold` (looked up from their criteria list) rather than falling back to `DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD=0.95`, or explicitly document that all DET advisories are structurally deferred by the apply-now rule.","cohort":["E4"],"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["orchestrator.py lines 412-424: DET-advisory findings are assembled with only {decision, severity, priority=0.4, validity, impact, tier='DET'} — no block_threshold key.","review_kernel/decide.py:53: DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD = 0.95","Plan text: 'An advisory is apply-now iff priority >= block_threshold - APPLY_NOW_MARGIN ... APPLY_NOW_MARGIN default 0.10'","0.4 < 0.95 - 0.10 = 0.85, so all DET advisories always land in defer under the stated rule."],"finding":"The plan asserts 'block_threshold (the finding's criterion blocking waterline; on the decided finding, else fall back to the registry DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD)' without disclosing that DET-tier advisory findings — which are assembled in orchestrator.partition_findings with hardcoded priority=0.4 and no block_threshold field — always exercise the fallback, yielding DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD=0.95. With APPLY_NOW_MARGIN=0.10, the apply-now condition (priority >= 0.95 - 0.10 = 0.85) is never met for any DET advisory (priority=0.4 << 0.85), so all DET advisories are structurally deferred. This behavioural consequence of the fallback path is unacknowledged in the plan and may surprise reviewers of R6's output.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe94e7dc4968c8627","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"What / The ranking rule — 'block_threshold (the finding's criterion blocking waterline; on the decided finding, else fall back to the registry DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD)'","norm_id":"n22d1de110a927f57","priority":0.33,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A DET advisory (e.g. P4/P6/P7 finding, priority=0.4) is always triaged as 'defer' regardless of how critical it may be, because the fallback block_threshold of 0.95 puts the apply-now bar at 0.85. The plan never flags this as expected behaviour.","A reviewer inspecting the triage output sees DET advisories consistently deferred and may not understand why — the fallback-to-DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD path is the reason, but it is opaque without this disclosure."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In the 'block_threshold' fallback clause, add: 'For DET-tier findings (which carry no block_threshold field), prefer a criterion-registry lookup by the finding's criteria[] before falling back to DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD — or explicitly document that DET advisories always defer.'","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify in the ordering rule that 'first criteria id' means the lexicographically smallest element of the criteria list (i.e. `min(criteria)`), or specify that `triage_advisories` normalizes each finding's criteria list to sorted order before comparing.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'sorted by priority DESC, then by the finding's first criteria id ASC, then by finding id ASC'","passes.py line 326: criteria list is filtered but not explicitly sorted before being placed on the finding dict (the filter preserves input order from the LLM)","orchestrator.py line 332: mint_finding_id uses sorted(criteria) for the hash, but does not re-sort the criteria list on the finding itself","ABSENCE: no statement in the plan that criteria lists are normalized to sorted order before triage_advisories consumes them"],"finding":"The ordering rule specifies tie-breaking by 'first criteria id ASC', but does not define what 'first' means for a finding with a multi-element criteria list. The codebase shows findings can carry multiple criteria (pass1_chunk filters but may keep multiple in-chunk criteria; mint_finding_id joins sorted criteria). If criteria lists are not guaranteed sorted, 'first' is non-deterministic across construction paths.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fea1b8769f88cfecf","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'Ordering (total, deterministic → byte-identical). All triaged advisories are sorted by priority DESC, then by the finding's first criteria id ASC'","norm_id":"na4b6434ac5f44b68","priority":0.264,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Two runs where the LLM emits criteria in different orders produce different triage orderings even for the same logical finding, breaking the byte-identical guarantee the plan claims.","A finding with criteria=['T8','E1'] vs criteria=['E1','T8'] would tie-break differently."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Change the ordering spec to 'tie-broken by min(criteria ids) ASC then finding id ASC' and have triage_advisories use `min(f.get('criteria') or [''])` as the tie-break key.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Simplify the triage attachment model to a single top-level `triage` list on the verdict output (parallel to `coaching`), each entry keyed by finding id with `bucket` (`apply-now`/`defer`), `priority`, and optional `triage_reason` — eliminating the dual per-note annotation + standalone-list representation.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan states both: 'each surviving-advisory coach note gains `triage` + optional `triage_reason`' AND 'advisories that mapped to no coach move still appear in the triage list keyed by finding id'","coach.py render_coach_notes returns a flat list of notes keyed by move/subject/finding_refs — there is no natural per-finding slot on a note that references multiple findings_refs","workflow_ops.py plan_review_coach already assembles a verdict dict with a top-level 'coaching' key — a parallel 'triage' key at the same level is the natural extension point and avoids the dual representation","The plan itself acknowledges the split: the 'keyed by finding id' fallback for uncoached advisories is a second data structure alongside the per-note annotation"],"finding":"The plan's triage attachment model introduces a dual representation: (a) per-coach-note `triage`/`triage_reason` annotation for findings that received a coach move, AND (b) a separate finding-keyed triage entry for advisory findings that mapped to no coach move. A structurally simpler alternative — a single top-level `triage` list on the verdict (parallel to `coaching`), each entry keyed by finding id with `bucket`, optional `triage_reason`, and `priority` — avoids the split, is natural for finding-level semantics, and removes the reconciliation burden from both the `plan_review_coach` render step and the test suite. The plan's current model requires the render step to merge two different data shapes, and forces tests to verify coherence between the per-note annotations and the standalone list.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f1411f610e5a24aa7","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What — 'The triage list is attached to the plan-review coaching output (each surviving-advisory coach note gains `triage` + optional `triage_reason`; advisories that mapped to no coach move still appear in the triage list keyed by finding id)'","norm_id":"n85f4d2a6ae2865bd","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A test verifying triage coverage must cross-check the per-note annotations against the standalone finding-keyed list to confirm every advisory appears exactly once — extra reconciliation not needed with a single list.","A coaching consumer (e.g. an agent reading the verdict) must know to look in two places (inside each coaching note AND in the standalone list) to get the full triage picture.","A coach note that references multiple finding_refs with different buckets has no clear `triage` value — the plan does not specify how the per-note annotation resolves this."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In the Scope section, replace 'each surviving-advisory coach note gains `triage` + optional `triage_reason`; advisories that mapped to no coach move still appear in the triage list keyed by finding id' with: 'triage_advisories emits a flat list [{finding_id, bucket, priority, triage_reason?}] over ALL surviving advisories; this list is attached as a top-level `triage` field on the plan_review_verdict (parallel to `coaching`), so every consumer has a single place to read the full triage picture regardless of whether a finding received a coach move.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Realign the leaf's mechanism to the parent's specification (MOVE_REGISTRY entry rendered deterministically), OR update the parent plan first to approve the pure-function architecture before re-reviewing this leaf.","cohort":["G7"],"criteria":["G7"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent (line 205): 'Add a move to the registry (rendered deterministically, like all moves): \"Triage each surviving advisory into the plan before claiming...\"'","Leaf (Mechanism choice section): 'It is NOT modelled as an entry in the Pass-4 MOVE_REGISTRY. The move registry's schema... structurally cannot express a ranked two-bucket split... So the triage is a small pure function...'"],"finding":"The leaf explicitly places the feature OUTSIDE the MOVE_REGISTRY, directly contradicting the parent's specified mechanism: 'Add a move to the registry (rendered deterministically, like all moves).'","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f452324b5abfcb02c","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Leaf: 'Mechanism choice' section ('It is NOT modelled as an entry in the Pass-4 MOVE_REGISTRY'); Parent: line 205 ('Add a move to the registry (rendered deterministically, like all moves)')","norm_id":"n6b50e97de75df31f","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer following the leaf adds a new pure function and per-finding stamp; an implementer following the parent adds a MOVE_REGISTRY entry. These are architecturally incompatible deliverables.","The leaf's rationale for deviating ('a single {subject} substitution structurally cannot express a ranked two-bucket split') changes the deliverable's semantics — machine bucketing vs. a human-coaching prompt — without updating the parent first."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Either: (a) implement the feature as a MOVE_REGISTRY entry as the parent specifies, adapting the template format to express the triage prompt to the author; or (b) update the parent's R6 'What' section to replace 'Add a move to the registry' with the pure-function approach, re-attest the parent, then re-review this leaf against the corrected parent.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a minimum-advisory-count threshold (defaulting to the parent's N≈5) to `triage_advisories` and document it in the ACs and docs, OR update the parent to remove/replace the threshold condition before re-reviewing.","cohort":["G7"],"criteria":["G7"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent (line 205): 'Attach it whenever ≥N advisories survive on a passing review (N≈5)'","Leaf 'What' section: triage runs on 'the round's surviving advisories' with no count-based eligibility condition stated","Leaf ACs: none of the six ACs reference a minimum-advisory-count threshold"],"finding":"The leaf silently drops the parent's ≥N advisory-count threshold (N≈5) that gates when the triage move attaches, delivering unconditional triage with no count guard.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc9d357805844c42d","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Leaf: 'What' section and Acceptance Criteria (no mention of N≈5 or any count threshold); Parent: line 205 ('Attach it whenever ≥N advisories survive on a passing review (N≈5)')","norm_id":"n2822d17f42c7f05a","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A review with a single surviving advisory would receive a triage list under the leaf's spec, but the parent intended the move to trigger only at meaningful advisory volume (≥5).","The APPLY_NOW_MARGIN bucketing with one advisory produces trivially thin output; the parent's N≈5 guard was presumably there to avoid noise on small advisory sets."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a `TRIAGE_MIN_ADVISORIES` named constant (default 5, matching the parent's N≈5) to `passes.py`; gate `triage_advisories` so it returns an empty/no-op result when the count of advisory findings is below this threshold. Add a corresponding AC and test.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Reconcile the leaf's automated-bucketing output with the parent's author-coaching-prompt model: either realign the leaf to emit a coaching note that prompts the author to self-triage (as the parent specifies), or update the parent to explicitly endorse automated bucketing as an alternative/augmentation.","cohort":["G7"],"criteria":["G7"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent (line 205): the move text is directed at the author — 'Triage each surviving advisory into the plan before claiming: apply it, or record a one-line deferral rationale in the description (see c8cc's Plan-review remediations section as the exemplar pattern)'","Leaf 'What': 'it partitions the round's surviving advisory findings into two buckets — apply-now and defer — using ONLY fields already recorded on each decided finding. It emits NO new LLM judgment... and no free prose'","The parent's move is a coaching prompt to the human author; the leaf's feature is an automated bucketing computation that replaces the author's judgment."],"finding":"The leaf redefines the deliverable's semantics: the parent specifies a coaching move that prompts the author to self-triage ('apply it, or record a one-line deferral rationale'); the leaf instead performs automated machine triage — bucketing findings into apply-now/defer — which is a different outcome and different user experience.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f89f0df104b8fc8a9","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Leaf: 'What' section ('partitions the round's surviving advisory findings into two buckets — apply-now and defer — using ONLY fields already recorded on each decided finding'); Parent: line 205 (move text: 'Triage each surviving advisory into the plan before claiming: apply it, or record a one-line deferral rationale in the description')","norm_id":"n3ed0eecd48914a86","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Under the parent's spec, the author reads a coaching note saying 'triage your advisories yourself before claiming'; under the leaf's spec, the system has already bucketed them and the author just sees a pre-sorted list. These have different effects on author engagement and latency.","The parent's FP-assessment relies on the move being 'pure coaching' that the author acts on; the leaf's automated bucketing changes the interaction model in a way the parent's falsifiable experiment did not account for."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Confirm R7 is either already shipped (cite the ticket/commit) or explicitly in-scope as a prerequisite/co-ship; if neither, add a fallback observable proxy (e.g. a manual spot-check protocol or a simpler count-of-apply-now-applied metric) so the 'no eval gate' posture has a concrete validation backstop.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'carries no detection risk, so per the epic gate table it ships first with no eval gate — validated post-ship by dogfooding via R7's advisory-application-latency metric'","AC5 quote: 'the R7 dogfood expectation (advisory-application latency observed via R7\\'s per-criterion metric)'","SotA doc lines 211–217 show R7 is a separate, independent recommendation ('a small offline job (not a gate change)') — its delivery is not guaranteed by this ticket","No search hit for 'advisory-application-latency' anywhere in the repo outside the SotA doc, confirming the metric does not yet exist"],"finding":"The plan's post-ship validation story depends on 'R7's advisory-application-latency metric', but R7 is a separate, unshipped recommendation from the same SotA doc. This is an unverified capability assertion: if R7 is not shipped (or not in scope), there is no stated validation path for the triage feature's effectiveness.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4dbcb3a0f02338f1","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Why section: 'validated post-ship by dogfooding via R7's advisory-application-latency metric' / AC5 (docs section): 'the R7 dogfood expectation (advisory-application latency observed via R7's per-criterion metric)'","norm_id":"n9bc204f608a98793","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["R7 ships after R6, or never ships — R6's triage feature has no validation substrate and no fallback measurement approach is stated.","A reviewer or auditor asks 'how do we know triage is working?' and the answer is 'depends on an unshipped job' — the plan has no observable proxy that does not require R7."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Assert the post-rollback schema state for verdicts already written with `triage`/`triage_reason` fields (e.g., confirm all verdict consumers tolerate unknown fields via `extra='ignore'` or equivalent, OR add a compensating-forward migration note that strips orphaned fields on rollback).","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'so the annotation reaches the persisted verdict' — the verdict is explicitly persisted","'each surviving-advisory coach note gains `triage` + optional `triage_reason`' — new fields added to persisted documents","'no config flag' — no mechanism to suppress new fields during a partial rollout or rollback window","ABSENCE: the plan never asserts the schema state of already-written verdicts after a rollback"],"finding":"The plan adds `triage` and `triage_reason` fields to the persisted verdict format with no config flag and no assertion about post-rollback schema state. If the code is rolled back after some verdicts have been written with the new fields, the plan is silent on whether those records remain valid/readable and what state the persisted schema is in — violating the T11(e) POST-ROLLBACK SCHEMA STATE requirement.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8a959d6f9c97517e","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section / Scope (`workflow_ops.py` wiring) / AC: 'Landed through Gerrit directly … no config flag'","norm_id":"n0b20c3dfdd17a7d8","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A batch of reviews runs with the new code, writing verdicts containing `triage`/`triage_reason`; the code is then rolled back. Any consumer that does strict schema validation (e.g., a Pydantic model without `extra='ignore'`) will fail to deserialize those now-orphaned fields, or silently carry unexpected data.","A monitoring query that selects `verdict.triage` from persisted records before and after rollback produces inconsistent results, with no documented remediation path."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a brief rollback note to the Scope or AC: 'Verdict consumers MUST be validated to tolerate unknown fields (e.g., Pydantic `extra=\"ignore\"`) before landing; on rollback, pre-existing `triage`/`triage_reason` fields in the store are inert and do not require cleanup.' If strict schema enforcement exists, add a compensating-forward step that removes the new fields on rollback.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (with a `-k defer_reason` proving command) that pins the `triage_reason` string against the exact format template specified in 'What' (fixed tokens + numeric fields only, e.g. `deferred: priority {p:.2f} is {delta:.2f} below its {bt:.2f} block line`) for at least two sample inputs.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"Each `defer` advisory carries a one-line `triage_reason` built only from its own numeric fields, e.g. `deferred: priority 0.32 is 0.28 below its 0.60 block line` (fixed words + the finding's recorded numbers — no LLM prose, trivially non-prescriptive)\"","ABSENCE: no AC line reads 'defer-reason format' or includes a -k defer_reason proving command"],"finding":"The 'What' section specifies a locked defer-reason format string (e.g. `deferred: priority 0.32 is 0.28 below its 0.60 block line`) and calls it a core deliverable property ('no LLM prose, trivially non-prescriptive'), but no acceptance criterion verifies the defer-reason format or pins its output against the specified template.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f89a97d1b8d366407","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section (Defer reason paragraph); Acceptance Criteria (no covering AC)","norm_id":"nab6d20307f8ed6ae","priority":0.1886,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An implementer ships a defer-reason that embeds LLM-generated prose or uses a different template, violating the 'locked format' promise, but all four existing ACs still pass.","The defer-reason format drifts between runs (non-deterministic due to float formatting), but only the top-level determinism AC (which tests rendered text, not per-finding reason strings) would catch it — only if the test is written broadly enough."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add to AC: `- [ ] The `triage_reason` string matches the template `deferred: priority {p:.2f} is {delta:.2f} below its {bt:.2f} block line` (exact fixed tokens, no prose); a parametrized test asserts the exact string for ≥2 inputs. Proving command: `python -m pytest tests/test_plan_review_triage.py -k defer_reason -q`.`","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Extend the `docs/plan-review-gate.md` AC to require a brief note on why `triage_advisories` is a plan-review-local pure function and NOT a `MOVE_REGISTRY` entry (the collective-rendering constraint), so future maintainers have an authoritative, persistent record of this design boundary.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T5e","T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan prose: 'It is NOT modelled as an entry in the Pass-4 MOVE_REGISTRY ... a single {subject} substitution structurally cannot express a ranked two-bucket split across all surviving advisories'","AC for docs: 'document the triage stage, its ranking rule (the APPLY_NOW_MARGIN default, the ordering, the defer-reason format), and the R7 dogfood expectation' — no mention of documenting the MOVE_REGISTRY exclusion rationale","ABSENCE: no ADR or CLAUDE.md update is scoped for the architectural decision"],"finding":"The novel architectural decision — why `triage_advisories` is implemented as a plan-review-local pure function rather than as a `MOVE_REGISTRY` entry — is explained in the plan ticket prose but the doc AC for `docs/plan-review-gate.md` does not require capturing this rationale in the persistent design doc. Future maintainers will lack the context to resist migrating the triage into MOVE_REGISTRY incorrectly.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fcc5a1d3cebcc1644","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What — Mechanism choice (rationale) section; ## Acceptance Criteria — docs/plan-review-gate.md bullet","norm_id":"nbd41b8c7f1fba57b","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future engineer reads docs/plan-review-gate.md, sees no MOVE_REGISTRY entry for triage, and opens a refactor ticket to 'unify' it into the registry — breaking the two-bucket collective rendering.","A reviewer of a later pass queries why triage bypasses the registry and finds no authoritative explanation in the persistent docs."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence to the docs AC: 'Include a design-note paragraph explaining why the triage stage is implemented as a plan-review-local pure function rather than a MOVE_REGISTRY move (the {subject}-per-finding template cannot express a collective two-bucket split), so future maintainers do not inadvertently migrate it into the registry.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Revise the title (and parenthetical) to accurately reflect that the triage stage is a standalone pure function on the Pass-4 path, NOT a MOVE_REGISTRY entry — e.g. 'advisory-triage stage (Pass-4 coach path, ship-first)' — so title and body are consistent.","cohort":["E3","G5","T6"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Title: 'advisory-triage coaching move (pass-4 registry, ship-first)'","Body: 'It is NOT modelled as an entry in the Pass-4 MOVE_REGISTRY'","The parenthetical '(pass-4 registry, ship-first)' in the title implies registry placement, directly contradicting the body's explicit architectural decision."],"finding":"The plan title calls this an 'advisory-triage coaching move' while the body explicitly states 'It is NOT modelled as an entry in the Pass-4 MOVE_REGISTRY' — creating a terminology contradiction that could mislead an implementer into attempting a registry entry before reading the rationale.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4f7422867c0477bc","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Title / 'Mechanism choice (rationale)' section","norm_id":"na155eff8fb33da06","priority":0.1132,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementer reads the title, starts implementing a MOVE_REGISTRY entry, then must reverse course upon reading the rationale — wasted work and possible confusion about the authoritative approach.","A future reader scanning only the title and AC misunderstands the architectural placement of the triage stage."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Change title to: 'R6: advisory-triage stage (Pass-4 coach path, ship-first)' and remove or reword the parenthetical '(pass-4 registry, …)' that implies registry placement.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E2","E6","F1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The ranking rule that determines 'apply-now vs defer-with-reason' assignment is never defined in the plan. The plan names the inputs (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status) but never specifies how they combine or which takes precedence, meaning the executor must design the algorithm themselves — a real design decision deferred rather than a defaultable gap.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"febacdc27cb5cf393","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)') and AC2 ('orders advisories by the documented ranking rule, pinned by test')","norm_id":"n2a75fe8930426fa2","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a 'Ranking rule' subsection to the What or Scope section, e.g.: 'Sort surviving advisories by (1) priority descending, (2) criteria-tier severity descending, (3) remediation-mode carryover status (carried > new). An advisory is apply-now if priority ≥ HIGH or criteria-tier = blocking-tier; otherwise defer-with-reason. Ties broken by finding ID for determinism.' Then reference this exact rule in AC2.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"no","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The 'apply-now vs defer-with-reason' ranking rule — the core novelty of this move — is never defined in the plan. The three inputs are named (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status) but no algorithm for combining them into buckets is specified. The deterministic/byte-identical claim in AC1 and the unit-test ordering pin in AC2 are unachievable without this rule being pinned; an implementer must invent it, introducing non-determinism at the plan level.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ffe0a05e876249faa","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section / AC1 ('same verdict -> byte-identical note') / AC2 ('orders advisories by the documented ranking rule, pinned by test')","norm_id":"n848878809c1101e5","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a 'Ranking rule' subsection to the plan's What section. For example: 'apply-now if priority ≥ 0.5 OR criteria tier is blocking-eligible; defer-with-reason otherwise; remediation-mode carryover status (True/False per finding) breaks ties toward apply-now.' Pin the exact thresholds so the unit test is verifying a reviewed spec, not an implementer's choice.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"no","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The 'ranking rule' that assigns each advisory to 'apply-now' vs 'defer-with-reason' is never defined anywhere in the plan. The plan names three inputs (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status) but specifies no decision function — no thresholds, no ordering formula, no tie-breaking. AC2 requires the rule be 'documented' and 'pinned by test', yet a test can only pin a rule that is stated.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f644bd06bd8785ae7","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets using only recorded finding fields'); AC2 ('the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule')","norm_id":"nef8dbb6ba0de037e","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a rule table, e.g.: apply-now if (priority ≥ P_THRESHOLD) OR (criteria_tier == 'blocking-capable' AND carryover) else defer-with-reason. Specify P_THRESHOLD value, the enumeration of 'criteria tier' values, and what 'carryover status = true' means on a finding record.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"no","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan describes the new move as ranking surviving advisories into 'apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets' — a collective, multi-finding output. The existing `render_coach_notes` / `coach_listing` mechanism renders one note per finding from a per-finding `{subject}` template. A move that produces a ranked triage of all advisories collectively does not fit the existing `MoveRegistry` schema (`{subject}` placeholder, per-finding) and would require new rendering logic — constituting behavioral CREATION beyond a registry addition.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f261487feb7a53f76","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets'","norm_id":"n1eac492e5d2e302d","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"no","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["A1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan describes the triage move as ordering 'the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets' — an aggregate/group output across multiple findings — but the existing template contract (review_kernel/coach.py render_coach_notes) is strictly per-finding: each CoachNote maps to one {subject} substitution, and coach_listing instructs 'Emit one note per finding you can map to a useful move.' Expressing a two-bucket ranking of all surviving advisories in a single locked template with a single {subject} placeholder is not possible without either bending the per-finding semantics or adding a new aggregate-render path that does not exist in the codebase, which would be an unplanned abstraction.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f1b650836e79cc5dd","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What / Acceptance Criteria AC1 ('the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule')","norm_id":"n61fea2b7975d07b0","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Reframe the move as a per-finding label: e.g., a template 'Apply {subject} in this session — priority warrants immediate action.' vs a separate move 'Defer {subject} to a follow-on ticket — lower priority.' Both fit the existing {subject} contract and together achieve the triage effect without a new render path.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"no","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan asserts the advisory-triage move ranks advisories using 'remediation-mode carryover status' from 'recorded finding fields,' but surviving advisory findings at pass-4 time do NOT carry a carryover/novelty field in the current codebase.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2f4366ccfa005372","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'no new LLM judgment, template-rendered … using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)'","norm_id":"nce0a9737171aad5b","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Replace 'remediation-mode carryover status' in the ranking rule with an existing finding field (e.g. `tier` which distinguishes DET vs LLM, or document that a `novelty` field must be carried forward onto surviving findings as in-scope work for this ticket).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"no","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"'Remediation-mode carryover status' is cited as one of the three recorded finding fields used for ranking, but this field is not present on the finding dicts that Pass-4 receives. The `partition_findings` output (`surfaced`, `blocking`) does not include a carryover field; carryover is a novelty-floor concept recorded in the sidecar but not propagated to the coach-facing finding objects.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fcc16ae31d41f0f95","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)'","norm_id":"nce5daea21cca29c5","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"no","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"'Remediation-mode carryover status' is asserted as a per-finding recorded field available at deterministic render time, but no such field exists on individual findings in the codebase. The finding schema (passes.py _pass1_model, orchestrator.py partition_findings) carries no remediation-mode attribute; remediation_mode_candidate() in attest.py is a ticket-level re-review eligibility predicate, not a per-finding annotation. If this field must be added to the finding schema, that is an unspecified schema change with downstream attestation and sidecar implications.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7b737a434c72a93b","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)'","norm_id":"n68114843e35ec506","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"no","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The two-bucket aggregate output shape (a ranked list partitioned into apply-now / defer-with-reason across ALL surviving advisories) is structurally incompatible with the existing MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA and render path. Every existing registry move emits one coaching sentence per finding via template.format(subject=subject). The new move must produce an ordered cross-finding bucket list — a categorically different output — but the plan claims it is 'template-rendered like every registry move, subject to the existing C1 subject validator'.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9a7b54f1348fa190","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('template-rendered like every registry move'); Scope section (src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/coach.py); src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/coach.py:35-58 (MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA), coach.py:162-196 (render_coach_notes)","norm_id":"ne783259cd2175e19","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"no","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"'Remediation-mode carryover status' is referenced as one of the three ranking inputs (a 'recorded finding field') but is not a field on individual advisory finding records in the existing schema. The codebase shows remediation_mode_candidate() returns a gate-level eligibility dict ({eligible, reasons}) — not a per-finding attribute — and no existing finding schema includes a carryover status field.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f37a217969d654d26","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)');\nsrc/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py:182-210 (remediation_mode_candidate);\nsrc/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py:195-201 (surfaced_findings / carryover context)","norm_id":"nd641c9f61e238d2a","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"no","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The 'advisory-triage' move's intended output — a two-bucket ranked list of surviving advisories ('apply-now' vs 'defer-with-reason') — cannot be rendered by the existing {subject}-placeholder template schema that validate_move_registry enforces (raises if template lacks exactly one {subject}). A single noun-phrase substitution cannot produce an enumerated, ordered split across multiple finding ids. The plan says 'template-rendered like every registry move' and 'no new LLM judgment', but doesn't specify how a template that only accepts {subject} emits the described triage structure.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fefba3649218325e5","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section; AC line 1 ('The move renders deterministically from recorded finding fields')","norm_id":"n96d44a0ab82982db","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"If the intent is a single set-level coaching note, the move's template could be: 'Triage {subject} before claiming: apply high-priority advisories now; record a one-line deferral rationale in the description for the rest.' The {subject} would be a noun-phrase like 'the N surviving advisories'. The bucket-ordering detail (which are apply-now vs defer) would then be implicit (apply the higher-priority ones), not enumerated in the template output. Alternatively, describe a new rendering hook that passes additional fields beyond {subject} — but that requires a schema change that should be called out explicitly.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"no","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"